{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611352","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611352"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:09:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:09:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16207"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16207","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16207"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.33,0.07,0.07,0.03,0.5]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8898"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115378"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8898","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8898"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16207"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97381"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"8399"},{"type":"tags","id":"10640"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21175"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21178"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115378","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115378"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe breast contains specialized structures that develop under hormonal influence to enable lactation during pregnancy and the postpartum period.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the structural differences between breast ducts and lobules?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ducts are lined by stratified squamous epithelium while lobules have columnar epithelium","Ducts contain myoepithelial cells while lobules do not","Ducts respond to prolactin while lobules respond to oxytocin","Ducts branch during pregnancy while lobules remain constant in size","Ducts transport and store milk while lobules produce milk"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Educts transport and store milk while lobules produce milk\u003C/strong\u003E. Breast ducts are tube-like structures lined by columnar epithelium that transport milk from the secretory units to the nipple. Lobules are grape-like clusters of alveoli that produce and secrete milk during lactation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDucts contain myoepithelial cells while lobules do not\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as both ducts and lobules have myoepithelial cells that aid in milk ejection. \u003Cstrong\u003EDucts are lined by stratified squamous epithelium while lobules have columnar epithelium\u003C/strong\u003E is also incorrect since the ductal-lobular system consists of two layers: inner/luminal epithelial cells - cuboidal to columnar epithelium and outer/basal myoepithelial cells. \u003Cstrong\u003EDucts branch during pregnancy while lobules remain constant in size\u003C/strong\u003E is inaccurate because both structures undergo significant growth and development during pregnancy. \u003Cstrong\u003EDucts respond to prolactin while lobules respond to oxytocin\u003C/strong\u003E misrepresents the hormonal responses, as prolactin stimulates milk production in lobules while oxytocin causes contraction of myoepithelial cells in both structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe terminal duct lobular unit (TDLU) represents the functional unit of the breast, consisting of a terminal duct and its associated lobules. Both structures work together during lactation to produce and deliver milk to the nipple.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Breast ducts are tubes lined by columnar epithelium that transport milk from the lobules to the nipple.","Breast lobules are grape-like clusters of secretory alveoli that produce milk during lactation.","The terminal duct lobular unit (TDLU) is the functional unit of the breast, consisting of a terminal duct and its associated lobules."],"references":["Zucca-Matthes G, Urban C, Vallejo A. Anatomy of the nipple and breast ducts. Gland Surg. 2016 Feb;5(1):32-6. doi: 10.3978/j.issn.2227-684X.2015.05.10. PMID: 26855906; PMCID: PMC4716863.","Going JJ. Ductal-lobar organisation of human breast tissue, its relevance in disease and a research objective: vector mapping of parenchyma in complete breasts (the Astley Cooper project). Breast Cancer Res. 2006;8(4):107. doi: 10.1186/bcr1527. PMID: 16879731; PMCID: PMC1779472.","Khan YS, Fakoya AO, Sajjad H. Anatomy, Thorax, Mammary Gland. 2023 Dec 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31613446.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97381"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16207"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97381","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97381"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T14:03:53+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T14:06:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8898"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115378"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGrou